    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nThe `on_exit` callback takes about 4 seconds until executing on Windows. While waiting, pressing a motion key makes it execute immediately.\r\n\r\nThis delay is present on Windows, but not on other platforms. This delay is present when `pty` is set to `v:true`, but not when it's set to `v:false`.\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n```vim\r\nnvim --clean\r\n:edit example.vim\r\n```\r\nAdd the following lines:\r\n```vim\r\nlet command = ['rundll32.exe']  \" effectively a no-op\r\n\r\nfunction End(job, status, type)\r\n  echom 'End: ' .. strftime('%c')\r\nendfunction\r\n\r\nlet jobstart_options = {\r\n      \\   'pty': v:true,\r\n      \\   'on_exit': function('End')\r\n      \\ }\r\nechom 'Start: ' .. strftime('%c')\r\nlet jobnr = jobstart(command, jobstart_options)\r\n```\r\n\r\nSave and source the file.\r\n```vim\r\n:write\r\n:source %\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe start time prints, followed by the end time in about four seconds.\r\n\r\n```\r\nStart: 4/19/2023 12:41:14 PM\r\nEnd: 4/19/2023 12:41:18 PM\r\n```\r\n\r\nPressing a movement key immediately after sourcing causes the `on_exit` callback function to execute sooner.\r\n\r\n```vim\r\n:source %\r\n\" Press l to move the cursor right\r\n```\r\n\r\n```\r\nStart: 4/19/2023 12:43:07 PM\r\nEnd: 4/19/2023 12:43:07 PM\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nI expected the `on_exit` callback to execute sooner (in the case where no cursor movement was triggered immediately after sourcing).\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nNeovim 0.9.0\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nNo (9.0) when using term_start (pty option not available for Windows, but a pty is seemingly used)\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nWindows 11\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\ncmd.exe\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\n(empty)\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\n nvim-win64.zip",
